@REM==============================================================================

@node "FAMEHydra" "What is FAMEHydra ?"

                              @{b}What is FAMEHydra ?
                             ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

To explain what FAMEHydra is we must first explain what Hydra is.

Hydra is a bi-directional file transfer protocol designed by Joaquim H.
Homrighausen and Arjen G. Lentz. Hydra is similar to Bimodem, a proprietary
file transfer protocol. Hydra originated in the PC world.

This is the Amiga version originally ported to the Amiga by Olaf Barthel
(term).

Hydra also exists for the Atari ST.

Hydra can send and receive data (files) at the same time and also adds
a chat option.

FAMEHydra is developed from the original sources supplied with 'term'
by Olaf Barthel.

I have to thank Olaf Barthel for porting Hydra for the Amiga and releasing
the sources.

With these sources it was possible to implement Hydra to FAME, not as a
bad add-on, and because of this FAMEHydra could be implemented as a FIM
door directly to FAME, communicating over the FAMEDoorPort to @{"MainPart" link "MainPart.guide/Main"}.
This results in maximum efficiency and security. FAMEHydra is implemented
as deep as xpr.libraries. You can always open/close the node screen while
Hydra runs without any problems. A big "locking" mechanism is also integrated
to avoid bad errors.

FAMEHydra is also optimized to use AmigaOS library calls as often as possible
instead of ANSI-C linked code. This keeps code smaller and makesFAMEHydra more 
effective and faster.Faster maybe not in data throughput, because the other side 
must also have the same kind of faster code, but faster code is always very 
important for a multinode bbs, because faster code means less calculations and
Less CPU usage.

FAMEHydra is enhanced over the original Hydra. The Filerequester process
for example, which is needed to add on new files to a list of download files
the SysOp can use, is no longer dependant on the near data section of the
main process FAMEHydra. All saved implementations are removed and this
results in a FAMEHydra.FIM door which is able to be loaded resident into
memory without canceling any feature of Hydra.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "Installation" "How to install FAMEHydra"

                            @{b}How to install FAMEHydra
                           ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~@{ub}

FAMHydra will always be installed by the installer script for FAME
installation.
Because of this we don't need to explain how to install FAMEHydra!!!

FAMEHydra is a FAME Door (FIM) named: FAMEHydra.FIM.

It will be called from the @{"MainPart" link "MainPart.guide/Main"} via the SYSCMD: 'HYDRA'.

Normally FAMEHydra.FIM is located in:

'FAME:Doors/FAME/FAMEHydra/FAMEHydra.FIM'

@endnode

